-- India’s NTPC Seeks 7.25 Million Tons of Imported Steam Coal
-- B y   A r c h a n a   C h a u d h a r y
-- 2013-11-25T11:14:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-25/india-s-ntpc-seeks-7-25-million-tons-of-imported-steam-coal.html
NTPC Ltd. (NTPC) ,  India ’s largest
electricity generator, is seeking 7.25 million metric tons of
imported steam coal for 14 thermal power plants across the
country,  tender  documents posted on the company’s website show.  Offers have to be made by Dec. 18, while the due date for
price bids will be set later, according to the documents.  The state-run company, which may import 17 million tons of
thermal coal in the year ending March 31, plans to cut its
dependence on overseas supplies to 13 million tons by 2017,
chairman Arup Roy Choudhury said in July.  To contact the reporter on this story:
